In 1950 the city council petitioned for an alteration in the number and boundaries of the municipal wards, and a consequent change in the number of aldermen and councillors. The petition was successful, with an [[order in council]] made on 28 July dividing the city into twenty-eight wards:<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=38997 |date=18 August 1950 |startpage=4225 }}</ref>

